li>



<li><strong>Use the Correct Formula:</strong><br>The standard formula for t=
he area of a sector when the angle is given in degrees is:Area of the Secto=
r =3D (=CE=B8 / 360=C2=B0) =C3=97 =CF=80 =C3=97 r=C2=B2Here:<ul><li>=CE=B8 =
(theta) is the central angle in degrees</li><li>r is the radius of the circ=
le</li><li>=CF=80 is the constant approximately equal to 3.14159</li></ul>I=
f the angle is given in radians, you can use a slightly different formula:A=
